sentences: Jules Anton Deelder (24 November 1944 – 19 December 2019) was a Dutch poet, spoken word poet and writer.
His prominent role in the cultural life of Rotterdam earned him the nickname "night mayor of Rotterdam.
"In 1954, Deelders discovered jazz at the age of 9 when he first heard Chet Baker.
Deelder was the presenter of his own jazz radio show, Deelder Draait, on Arrow Jazz FM.
